    "body": "When running `gitk` generated by spack, I see the following error:\r\n```\r\n % gitk\r\n/scratch/vendors/spack.20170502/opt/spack/linux-rhel7-x86_64/gcc-4.8.5/git-2.12.2-cduatp5pegjyiwvv6rfmpdaagp2hlmct/bin/gitk: line 3: exec: wish: not found\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis can be remedied by:\r\n1.  Creating a symlink in the `tk` bin directory: \r\n```\r\ncd `spack location -i tk`/bin; ln -s wish8.6 wish\r\n```\r\n2. Loading the `tk` module when `git` is loaded.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure how to automate this in spack.\r\n",
